<!--
VOICING PLAN — 4157 That Men a Godly Life Might Live (C major / G)
Note: Hymn is in C but the ABC label says Key: C. Final note is G (m.11)
suggesting this has a modal ending on V. Harm labels use ⑤ as "I" of G.
Actually reviewing the ABC: final bar is G4, so this is C major ending on V.
The arrangement treats it as C major throughout.

Non-diatonic: Gm (G Bb D) → G major (V) — harp avoids Bb.
  Melody keeps Bb as accidental on staff 1 only.

Rhythmic interest: pickup m.0 establishes Em/C for a modal entry.
  Rests within measures (m.2 beat 3, m.5 beat 1, m.7 beat 3) create
  breathing space typical of the Lutheran chorale style.

TEXTURE ARC:
Pickup: sparse, 2-voice entry
mm.1-4: moderate, builds ii7→I cadence
mm.5-8: fuller, "333" ii7 in m.5 with D5 in RH
mm.9-11: final push G/Em → G final. Bb in melody not doubled by harp.
-->
